****************************************
* Disk Static Storage Global variable definitions
*   Required in static storage of all RBF device drivers

*  Note: This does not reserve any memory for drive tables.
*        Each driver is responsible for reserving sufficient
*        memory for the appropriate number of tables.

			org V_USER reserve system required
V_NDRV:		do.b 1 number of drives
			do.b 7 reserved
DRVBEG:		equ . beginning of drive tables

* Global storage for disk drive tables.
* Each table contains data copied from the first DD_SIZ bytes
* of sector zero (reformatted slightly), as well as the static
* variables defined here.

			org 0
* Copy of first DD_SIZ vars in device descriptor (sector zero)

			do.b 22 reserve 22 bytes for track zero information
V_TRAK:		do.w 1 current track
V_FileHd:	do.l 1 open file list for this drive
V_DiskID:	do.w 1 disk id
V_BMapSz:	do.w 1 bitmap  size
V_MapSct:	do.w 1 lowest bitmap sector to search
V_BMB:		do.w 1 Bit-map in use flag
V_ScZero:	do.l 1 Pointer to sector zero buffer
V_ZeroRd:	do.b 1 sector zero read flag
V_Init:		do.b 1 drive initialized flag
V_ResBit:	do.w 1 Reserved bitmap sector number (if any)
V_SoftEr:	do.l 1 Number of recoverable errors occurred
V_HardEr:	do.l 1 Number of non-recoverable errors occurred
V_Cache:	do.l 1 Drive cache queue head
V_DTExt:	do.l 1 Drive table extension ptr
V_MapMax:	do.w 1 maximum bitmap sector number
V_MapOffs:	do.w 1 bitmap sector offset
V_UseFlags: do.b 1 flags indicating device capabilites
			do.b 3 reserved
			do.l 4 reserved
DRVMEM:		equ .

******************
* Bit definitions for V_UseFlags
NoSSDelBlk_B: equ 0

******************
* constant definitions for V_UseFlags
NoSSDelBlk: equ 1
